enhanced_by.reason: Both methods modify the internal state of the Safelist by adding elements to the tagNames set and related maps.
Both methods involve modifying the internal state of the Safelist by adding or removing tags.
The isSafeTag method can be used to validate the output of addTags by checking if the added tags are now considered safe.
The removeTags method can be used to reverse the state change made by addTags, allowing for testing of rollback scenarios.
